            <section id="faq" class="prose mt-8">
              <h2>
                Frequently asked questions about Kentucky occupational tax
              </h2>

              <h3>What is the Kentucky occupational tax?</h3>
              <p>
                The Kentucky occupational tax (often called an
                <em>occupational license fee</em>) is a local tax imposed by
                many Kentucky cities and counties on wages, salaries, and net
                profits from business activity within their jurisdiction. It is
                <strong>separate</strong> from Kentucky state income tax and
                federal income tax.
              </p>

              <h3>Who has to pay Kentucky occupational tax?</h3>
              <p>
                Employees who work in a jurisdiction that levies an occupational
                tax usually have the tax withheld from their paycheck by their
                employer. Businesses, self‑employed individuals, and independent
                contractors may also owe occupational tax on net profits and
                must file returns directly with the local tax office.
              </p>

              <h3>Is the tax based on where I live or where I work?</h3>
              <p>
                Occupational tax is generally based on
                <strong>where you work</strong> and where your business activity
                occurs, not where you live. If you work in multiple
                jurisdictions, you may be subject to more than one occupational
                tax and should review each local ordinance carefully.
              </p>

              <h3>Are the same rates used everywhere in Kentucky?</h3>
              <p>
                No. Each city or county that imposes an occupational tax sets
                its own rate and rules. Some use a simple percentage of wages,
                others may have flat fees, caps, or special rules for certain
                types of income. Always check the official website or forms for
                the specific jurisdiction.
              </p>

              <h3>Does this calculator file my occupational tax return?</h3>
              <p>
                No. This tool only provides an estimate of local occupational
                tax and net pay. To file or pay occupational tax, you must use
                the official forms and payment methods provided by the relevant
                Kentucky city or county or by their occupational tax
                administrator.
              </p>
